        <h3 class="style7">Members per team</h3>
        <ul class="style7" type="none"><li class="style8">The number of members is limited to a maximum of five(5). Students from different colleges can also make a team.</li>
        </ul>
        </li>
        
        <li><h3 class="style7">Dimensions</h3>
            <ul><li class="style8" type="none">Each robot is to be no larger than 25cm length by 20cm width by 30cm height at the start.. The robot is not limited from deploying objects that make it wider or longer after the start. The robot can weigh no more than 1.5 kg.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>

        <li><h3 class="style7">Sensors</h3>
            <ul><li class="style8" type="none">Any type of sensors may be used.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>

        <li><h3 class="style7">Harmlessness</h3>
            <ul  type="none"><li class="style8"><p>At all times, robot behaviour must be non-offensive, non-destructive, and non-harmful to humans, robots, and the facilities.<br /><br /></p>
                                   <p>During inspection (and at any time during the event), the judges may require safety changes or other modifications to meet the harmlessness requirement. Harmful robots are either not allowed to compete at all or can later be disqualified if potential harmful issues are proven or revealed in battle. <br /><br /></p>
                                   <p>Judges will examine each robot to determine if the design is sufficient to survive the expected pushing, shoving, and physical rigors of the competition. Suggestions may be made to avoid damage to the robot. A weak robot will be allowed to compete at its own risk.</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </li>

        <li><h3 class="style7">Mini Sumo Robots must not:</h3>
            <ol class="style8"><li>Emit smoke or fire</li>
                <li>Leak, stain, or soil  </li>
                <li>Disperse powder, grit, or grime  </li>
                <li>Spray, throw, or use projectiles </li>
                <li>Jam, shock, or electromagnetically interfere</li>
                <li>Snare, entangle, or employ nets/rope</li>
                <li>Scratch, gouge, or scrape </li>
                <li>Mini Sumo Robots must not fly or generate lift to isolate themselves from the ring Surface.</li>
            </ol></li>
    </ol>
